The developers of Clifox are more than happy to assist those who wish to use Clifox.
Please remember to include your Linux distribution name and version with any issues involving installation.
The quickest method to receive support, or to discuss Clifox, is via IRC.
You can use your favorit IRC client, and access the #speakup channel on the Freenode network, accessible from irc.freenode.net.
You can use SIP, if you are familiar with it, and call:
3000@fs.reisers.ca.
You can subscribe to the Clifox mailing list, by sending a blank message to:
wb-subscribe@linux-speakup.org
You can also send bug reports and the like to:
clifox@bmcginty.us
